    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-21T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-21T04:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/398: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-21T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 21, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 21—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your telegram No. 8, March 18, 2 p.m., and 9, March 18, 7 p.m. In response to
                    oral representations the Legation is now assured that if the Egyptian
                    authorities find Insull on Egyptian soil he will be arrested and turned over to
                    us for deportation. If American authorities arrest him on Egyptian soil and
                    request Egyptian authorities to detain him this will be done upon a written
                    request and at our risk and responsibility.</p>
                <p>Egyptian authorities also suggest that the Legation state in writing that the
                    American Government is not interested in preventing his landing in Egypt and I
                    am doing so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
